oc:kn_30c06c10 a oc:DesignPrinciple,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When selecting data sources for programmatic pages" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Prioritize proprietary or product-derived data over public data—the defensibility hierarchy is: proprietary > product-derived > user-generated > licensed > public." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Public data is weakest because competitors can replicate it; proprietary data creates a moat that makes pages uniquely valuable and harder to outrank." .

oc:kn_3413d744 a oc:AntiPattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When reviewing programmatic SEO implementations" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Avoid these common mistakes: thin content (just swapping names), keyword cannibalization (multiple pages targeting same keyword), over-generation (pages with no search demand), poor data quality, and ignoring UX." ;
    oc:hasRationale "These are the top reasons programmatic SEO campaigns fail or get penalized by Google." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_4ca95b70 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:WorkflowStrategy ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When designing internal linking for programmatic pages" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Use hub-and-spoke internal linking: hub pages link to all programmatic spokes, spokes cross-link to related spokes, and every page has breadcrumbs with structured data." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Hub-and-spoke distributes authority from strong pages to programmatic pages and ensures crawlers can discover all pages." .

oc:kn_560441aa a oc:Heuristic,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When deciding page generation scope" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Better to have 100 great pages than 10,000 thin ones—start with high-volume patterns and ensure each page answers genuine search intent." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Google increasingly rewards quality and penalizes scale-for-scale's-sake; thin pages waste crawl budget and risk manual actions." .

oc:kn_8737b345 a oc:Constraint,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When designing URL structure for programmatic pages" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Use subfolders (yoursite.com/templates/resume/) not subdomains (templates.yoursite.com/resume/) for programmatic pages." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Subfolders consolidate domain authority while subdomains split it, weakening the SEO impact of all programmatic pages." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_ce30c9ef a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:PreFlightCheck ;
    oc:appliesToContext "At the beginning of any programmatic SEO engagement" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Before starting, check for .agents/product-marketing-context.md (or .claude/product-marketing-context.md) and use existing context before asking questions." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Product marketing context contains business details, audience, and positioning that prevents redundant questions and improves strategy quality." ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_e49a78bf a oc:AntiPattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When designing any programmatic page template" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Never create pages that just swap variable names in identical templates—each page must provide genuinely unique value beyond keyword substitution." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Google penalizes thin/doorway pages that offer no unique value, which destroys rankings for all programmatic pages on the domain." ;
    oc:severityLevel "CRITICAL" .

oc:kn_f25dc78f a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:PostFlightValidation ;
    oc:appliesToContext "Post-launch monitoring of programmatic pages" ;
    oc:directiveContent "After launch, monitor: indexation rate, rankings, traffic, engagement, conversion. Watch for thin content warnings, ranking drops, manual actions, and crawl errors." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Early detection of indexation or quality issues prevents cascading damage to the entire programmatic page set." .

